  "text": "The differential effects of drugs on G protein-and ␤arr-mediated signaling can explain some of their beneficial and detrimental effects. Deletion of ␤arr2 enhances morphine analgesia due to diminished desensitization of the -opioid receptor but reduces the detrimental side effect of constipation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Deletion of ␤arr1 does not affect the beneficial actions of nicotinic acid on lowering circulating triglycerides and raising high-density lipoproteins but attenuates the side effect of flushing, which is associated with burning and itching of the skin [CITATION_3] .",
